1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with bandwidth allocation for multicast/broadcast services over wireless networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper focuses on providing video services over wireless networks, which is a multimedia application. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a bandwidth allocation scheme that efficiently allocates bandwidth among different types of traffic, which involves information theory concepts. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a scheme to improve system performance by allocating variable bandwidths, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly deal with cryptography and security, it is possible that the proposed scheme may have implications for security and privacy in wireless networks.
